What fun! :-) To look at Princess Lollipop and wish that I were her is something you don't get to do everyday! ;-) It's still holds the trill of - Who's going to win? Is it me-or you? Well, this time it was them... not me. :-( How depressing! I think now we are going to play Set. That game Cristin bets me all the time... wait I just heard that we are going to play Bingo! Have you ever heard of the word, "Onomatopoeia"?

This is the new word I learned today:

Accolades.

Have you ever heard of it? I hadn't until I was reading a book and it had the word in it and I was like, "What does THAT word mean? Accolades?"

First off, Happy February!

And then second off, I'm sick!:-( :-( Jonathan has been sick for about 2 weeks, he still has a lingering cough. :-( Then Daniel and Michelle got sick. :-( Then on Monday, Amy and I got sick.:-( Then today, Mom and Cristin got sick... :-( I don't think that we are at ALL sick! ;-) :: Cough, cough!:: (Those last two coughs really happened! :-)

Lord willing, we are going to watch Sheffy tonight, since I can't go to my flute lesson (Sorry Bethany! :-) and I don't want to get EVERYONE exposed at SWORD, so that means WE ARE STAYING HOME TONIGHT!!! :-) :-) :-)  I'll NEVER get tired of that movie! It's always encouraging! :-) Have you ever watched it? :-)

Got to go, dinners ready... Chili, bread, and vanilla pudding! Yum! :-)

Sick Sarah
I was just wondering, When was the last time YOU had your birthday on a Sunday? :-)

Oh, btw...

my "new" favorite color is Purple!!!!

I had an awesome breakfast with my Grandpa's! When Dad was alive, he would take out us children for our Birthday's, but since the Lord called him home, our Grandpa's take us out. I think that we kids, Jonathan, Cristin, Amy, Daniel, Michelle, and Me have the BEST Grandparents in the WORLD!!!!!!! :-)

Here is a picture (link to the picture!) of my Grandpa's and me (after we ate.)

http://tinypic.com/jr5zb6.jpg

When we got done eating, my Grandpa's took me to the store to get something flowery for my Mama, in the end I got Mama, a petite white rose plant. I liked it a lot but, I wasn't sure is Mama would like it, but she did! You might wonder, why on earth I would give Mama a rose plant on my birthday, the reason being... It's a way that I could say, 'Thank You', to her for giving birth to me. :-)

I'm SOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO blessed to have such a WONDERFUL family, it's not even funny! All of my family, like my Cousin's, Aunt's, Uncle's, and Grandparents all claim that they follow the Lord. Which is SUCH a blessing. For when we get together, we are not that shy, cause we all know where we stand. We do have are different standards, and stuff, but the main thing is:

That the follow and love the Lord with a happy heart!  

I better be going! I just wanted to post a BIG 'Thank You' to all those who have/said that will, give me a birthday card! How VERY thougthful you guy's (GIRL'S!!! ;-)  are! You just make me smile! :-) :-) :-) :-) :-) :-) I think that you get the point! ;-)

~Sarah

P.S. I hope that some of the stuff make since! :-) Or I might just be going CRAZY!!!                                                                              

P.P.S. I'll keep my bargin, Bethany! :-)

I CAN'T BELEIVE THAT MY BIRTHDAY IS TOMORROW!!!!!!!!

I'm going to be old... 15! ;-)

I'm getting lots of nice cards from my friends! :-) I turely feel loved!

Happy Birthday to a dear friend of mine,

Hannah R.

Happy Birthday Hannah! Hope you have a blessed birthday!

~Sarah

Well, for the last week... the internet hasn't been working. Until now, of course! :) Last Wednesday, (Not yesterday. The week before that.) the internet stopped working. Jonathan worked on it, but it still didn't work. :( On Friday, Jonathan "MADE" (not really.) me call tech-support. I, Sarah Anne McIntire, called tech-support! Wow! I was amazed! I got REALLLLLLLLY nice people, thankfully. I hope I don't have to do it again... any time soon, any way! :)

I hope that ALLL of you had a Wonderful Christmas season.

Until next time...

Sarah

P.S. Hopefully, next post I'll tell what I got for Christmas! :-) YEAH!

Thanks to the Lord, I'm not sick yet! :) The Lord is SOOO good! We have SOOOOOOOOO many thing to be greatful about. My Cup is TURLY overflowing with many blessings!

Wow. Christmas is JUST around the corner. So, with that  in mind, What are you going to do for Christmas? :) This might be the last time I post before Christmas so...

MERRY  CHRISTMAS!!!

Sarah
P.S. Remember, Jesus is the Reason for the Season!

Here is My doleful tale... (Well, not a REALLY doleful tale!)

I was getting to bed pretty late every night this last week. But on Sunday, I was just a human-being, doing nothing but living (maybe not even that! ;)! In other words... tired!!!!!  After a LONG day on Sunday, I came home and was helped unload our car. When Daniel called out... "Sarah, can you come rub my legs?" ...I answered back, saying I will as soon as I can. I went to D-boy's bed (Daniel), and instead of rubbing his legs, talked with Him. Then he said that he need to talk to mom. I really think he wanted to get out of bed, but who knows! ;-) And when he came back he pleaded me to stay for just a FEW seconds, so I did... ...a WHOLE night! I woke up in the middle of the night with D-boy's legs, kicking me! No, I wanted my bed, but I was just toooooo tired to go to my bed. So I paid for it today!  I hope that I can get a REALLY good sleep tonight!

Sarah

P.S. Today, if my Dad where alive, He would have been the BIG 5-0! You can pray for us, and Grandparents. Thanks!

I was wondering what YOUR fav. candy is? Can You tell me? :-)

Sarah
With the wind whipping around our house, I'm ready to crawl into bed, with TON's of covers! :-) Off I go!

I can hardly wait till Christmas comes, cause I LOVE giving things! :-) I also LOVE Thanksgiving, because we can give thanks to our Creator! 

Got to go!

Sarah

P.S. Have you ever heard of this song: Happy Xmas (War Is Over), by The Three Tenors? If you never heard them sing it,  you sure are missing out! ;-)

Ttfn, Ta ta for now!

Sarah
